                <h3>Î£Ï…Î¼Ï€Î­ÏÎ±ÏƒÎ¼Î±</h3>
                <p>Î¤Î·Î½ ÎµÏ€ÏŒÎ¼ÎµÎ½Î· Ï†Î¿ÏÎ¬ Ï€Î¿Ï… Î¸Î± ÎºÎ¿Î¹Ï„Î¬Î¾ÎµÏ„Îµ Î­Î½Î± Î´Î¹Î¬Î³ÏÎ±Î¼Î¼Î±, Î¼Î·Î½ ÏˆÎ¬Ï‡Î½ÎµÏ„Îµ Î³Î¹Î± "Î¼Î¿Ï„Î¯Î²Î±". Î¨Î¬Î¾Ï„Îµ Î³Î¹Î± Ï„Î¿Ï…Ï‚ Î±Î½Î¸ÏÏÏ€Î¿Ï…Ï‚.</p>
                <p>Î¡Ï‰Ï„Î®ÏƒÏ„Îµ Ï„Î¿Î½ ÎµÎ±Ï…Ï„ÏŒ ÏƒÎ±Ï‚: <strong>Î Î¿Î¹Î¿Ï‚ Î­Ï‡ÎµÎ¹ Ï„Î¿Î½ Î­Î»ÎµÎ³Ï‡Î¿ Ï„ÏÏÎ±;</strong> Î— Î±Î³Î¿ÏÎ¬ ÎµÎ¯Î½Î±Î¹ Î±Ï€Î»ÏÏ‚ Î¼Î¹Î± Î±Î½Ï„Î±Î½Î¬ÎºÎ»Î±ÏƒÎ· Ï„Î·Ï‚ Î±Î½Î¸ÏÏÏ€Î¹Î½Î·Ï‚ Ï€Î¯ÏƒÏ„Î·Ï‚, Ï„Î¿Ï… Ï†ÏŒÎ²Î¿Ï… ÎºÎ±Î¹ Ï„Î·Ï‚ Î±Î¹ÏƒÎ¹Î¿Î´Î¿Î¾Î¯Î±Ï‚.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="lang-en">
                <p>When you look at a stock chart, what do you see? Red and green lines? Confusing patterns?</p>
                <p>Most people think trading is about memorizing complex shapes or predicting the future with "technical analysis."</p>

                <div class="highlight-box">
                    <strong>They are wrong.</strong> The stock market isn't a math problem. Itâ€™s an <strong>auction</strong>. And once you understand the auction, the charts stop being confusing lines and start telling a story.
                </div>

                <h3>1. The Tug-of-War: Supply vs. Demand</h3>
                <p>Imagine a crowded market.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>The Buyers (Bulls):</strong> They want to buy shares because they think the price will go <em>up</em>.</li>
                    <li><strong>The Sellers (Bears):</strong> They want to sell shares because they think the price will go <em>down</em> (or they want to cash out).</li>
                </ul>
                <p><strong>The Price</strong> is simply the point where they agree to trade at this exact second.</p>
                <p>If there are <strong>more aggressive buyers</strong>, price goes UP. If there are <strong>more aggressive sellers</strong>, price goes DOWN.</p>

                <h3>2. What actually moves the needle?</h3>
                <p>Why would buyers suddenly become aggressive? Two main reasons:</p>
                <ol>
                    <li><strong>Fundamentals (The Logic):</strong> A company releases a great report. Investors rush to buy. Demand goes up -> Price goes up.</li>
                    <li><strong>Psychology (The Emotion):</strong> Fear and Greed. Sometimes, nothing has changed in the company, but people are scared of a war. They panic and sell. Supply floods the market -> Price crashes.</li>
                </ol>

                <h3>3. Reading the Story (The Candlesticks)</h3>
                <p>This is where "Candlesticks" come in. They are not magic symbols. They are a <strong>Battle Report</strong>.</p>
                <p>Every candle tells you who won the battle during a specific time.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Green Body:</strong> The price closed higher than it opened. The Buyers won today.</li>
                    <li><strong>Red Body:</strong> The price closed lower than it opened. The Sellers took control.</li>
                    <li><strong>The Wicks:</strong> These show the <em>struggle</em>. A long wick at the bottom means sellers tried to push the price down, but buyers were strong enough to push it back up.</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Conclusion</h3>
                <p>Next time you look at a chart, donâ€™t look for "patterns." Look for the people.</p>
                <p>Ask yourself: <strong>Who is in control right now?</strong> The market is just a reflection of human belief, fear, and optimism.</p>
            </div>

        </div>
    </article>
</div>

<script>
    /* Javascript Î³Î¹Î± Î‘Î»Î»Î±Î³Î® Î“Î»ÏÏƒÏƒÎ±Ï‚ & Theme (Î‘ÎºÏÎ¹Î²ÏÏ‚ Î¯Î´Î¹Î± Î»Î¿Î³Î¹ÎºÎ® Î¼Îµ Ï„Î¿ index) */
    function toggleLanguage() {
        const body = document.body;
        if (body.classList.contains('english-mode')) {
            body.classList.remove('english-mode');
        } else {
            body.classList.add('english-mode');
        }
    }

    function toggleTheme() {
        const body = document.body;
        const icon = document.getElementById('theme-icon');
        if (body.getAttribute('data-theme') === 'dark') {
            body.removeAttribute('data-theme');
            icon.classList.remove('fa-sun'); icon.classList.add('fa-moon');
        } else {
            body.setAttribute('data-theme', 'dark');
            icon.classList.remove('fa-moon'); icon.classList.add('fa-sun');
        }
    }
</script>

